			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Dire Charm
<br />
Re-Use Time: 1 hour 12 minutes
<br />
This ability allows the Magician to charm any summoned NPC in the zone of level 46 or lower. 
<br />
The charm lasts until the player zones or either the player or charmed NPC dies. 
<br />
This charm is done via a hotkey and does not require mana or memorization of a spell. 
<br />
It can be used once every 72 minutes.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
What's so wrong with this?  Druids, Enchanters, Necros all get it.  Wizards don't get it, but it would be understandable since they don't "control" any elements and only channel them.  Beastlords wouldn't get this since they are more melee than caster.  I don't believe that it would be any more powerful than what the other classes receive.  I can think the only issue would be that the DPS from our spells would make us overpowered compared to them.  What if our Dire Charm went like this:
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Dire Charm
<br />
Re-Use Time: 1 hour 12 minutes
<br />
This ability allows the Magician to charm any summoned NPC in the zone of level 46 or lower. 
<br />
The charm lasts until the player zones or either the player or charmed NPC dies. 
<br />
<span style="color: red">While the summoned NPC is charmed, Magician spell damage is decreased.  
<br />
(*Suggest: 20 to 30 percent*)</span>
<br />
This charm is done via a hotkey and does not require mana or memorization of a spell. 
<br />
It can be used once every 72 minutes.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Same ability and brings our spell damage output in line with the other classes have while we have a DC pet.  Tell me if I'm wrong or suggestions to improve it.  I personally think we should have something like this.<br />_________________<br />~Maegana
<br />
Arch Convoker of the Sworn Few on Povar<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=716438" target="_new">
<br />
Click for my Magelo</a> 
<br />
"When the possibilities are endless, why settle for second best?"</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
