			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Mages need a way to reduce aggro, that is one of the main reasons that mage dps is so much lower, If we attempt to nuke more than a few times we are summoned and killed quickly. The reason if you think about it is easy to understand. Aggro is based on the hate list, mages have very good DPS and as such we raise quickly to the top of the list and summoned and killed once we are on the top. There is no way to stop this unless we stop nuking, while a wizard would be the top of that list, their concussion spells lowers it so a mage moves up to the top. As long as the main tank maintains aggro we have a little more flexability to nuke, but not a lot. Our nuke damage grows and with no way to lower it, we are prime bait to be summoned and killed. 
<br />

<br />
This is the problem as many see it in the elemental planes and beyound, it isn't that we don't have a decent nuke to lay down damage, it is the fact those nukes generate too much aggro, and with no way to reduce it, we are just not a class that guilds will recruit for the nuking role. Simply put, we can do it, but because of aggro we can't and thus not needed as a main class to deliver DPS in a raid situation.
<br />

<br />
A way to reduce aggro from our nuke is not over powering in anyway what so ever, if you think about it. In an exp group I can nuke enough to kill mobs and being summoned is not a concern. The issue is aggro on raids, and mage aggro is way over what it should be compaired to others. 
<br />

<br />
SoE knows this, every guild knows that. Mages needed usaually 1 and wizards are unlimited because of concussion. If you remember when concussion was introduced it was because wizard aggro was huge and theywere not doing damage as they were being killed too rapidly, the same issue mages face today.
<br />

<br />
We need help to get that aggro down, and not by casting a rain spell that will not net us much increased DPS, but a way to let our DPS grow to close the gap on wizards by nuking with the spells we already have. If we could nuke as often as a wizard we will do the damage SoE always imagined we should do, the point is, we just need a means to do it.
<br />

<br />
Calebe</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
