			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Charm for magicians is a bittersweet thing. Consider that under normal circumstances you have a perfectly safe doting pet that waits on you hand and foot. He hits around 80s, quads, and does somewhere from 60-90 DPS fully hasted.
<br />

<br />
Now, one can go out and charm just about any elemental out there. However, exactally why would you? Compared to your uber safe pet, a dire charmie may be more risk than you want to deal with, and his damage output isn't all that great anyways. Oh, we can make it better, but still, it's barely better than ubersafe pet.
<br />

<br />
When charm is very usefull is when the pets you're charming exceed, by a large margin, the damage output of your pet. Something in the order of 200+ DPS (standard takish 368 quadding pet). Until that point, you trade risk for meager improvements in damage, and frankly, that's not something that's worth it to me.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
